HEADWORD: Eardrop
<hw>Ear"drop`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
pendant for the ear; an earring; <as>as, a pair of
<ex>eardrops</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species of primrose. See
<er>Auricula</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eardrum</ent>⟦br⟧
